description: Local checkout is the source of truth and requires explicit handoff
alwaysApply: true
---

# Local Handoff Workflow

- Treat `E:\dev\hub` as the source of truth between turns.
- Read the local version of a touched file before changing it.
- Scratch/worktree edits are temporary working space only.
- Before finishing, sync every touched file back to `E:\dev\hub`.
- Do not mark work complete until the touched files are back in local.

# Confirm Before Editing

- Before substantial edits, briefly state:
  - the decision
  - the files to change
  - the expected impact
- Do not start major code changes before stating that plan.

# Review Handoff

- Stop after local files are updated so the user can review and continue editing.
- If the user edits local files afterward, those local edits become the new source of truth next turn.
- If local and scratch differ, prefer local unless the user explicitly says otherwise.
